Author: Artificer <w-mo81bdcc-18d15cf356eb@nexus.local>
Date:   Tue Apr 21 03:20:00 2026 +0000

    feat(spider): add engine-failure stuck cause with retryable flag

    Records an observability payload on writs stuck by engine failures so a
    future retry clockwork can distinguish transient crashes from definitional
    errors without re-deriving the cause from rig state.

    - Add 'engine-failure' to SpiderStuckCause covering all non-dependency
      engine failures (session crashes, engine throws, graft invalid, unknown
      design/block type, non-serializable yields, etc.)
    - Add optional retryable and detail fields to SpiderWritStatus, written
      at every failEngine call site
    - Guard autoUnstick to only act on 'failed-blocker' and 'cycle' so
      engine-failure writs are left for retry clockwork
    - Export SpiderStuckCause and SpiderWritStatus publicly for consumers
    - Cover each failEngine path, retryable classification, and autoUnstick
      scope with unit tests
    - Update README and architecture spec

